&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-4200&quot; title=&quot;Minor issue with throttle argument in kafka-reassign-partitions.sh&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;KAFKA-4200&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;KAFKA-4200&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: kafka-reassign-partitions &#8212;-verify prints &quot;Throttle was removed&quot; regardless of whether a throttle was applied. It should only print this if the value was actually changed. Tested this maually ensuring the value is not printed when we call verify whilst the rebalance is running, but does print the value when running verify when the throttle completes. Rerunning verify after the throttle completes also does not print the line.&lt;/p&gt;

